cs.HC, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on studying non-verbal social signals in job interviews, which is a human-computer interaction scenario. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is also likely as the paper uses deep learning methods to analyze video interviews. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is relevant as the paper deals with analyzing language in job interviews, but it is less likely than cs.CV as the focus is on non-verbal behavior. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper uses machine learning methods, but it is less likely than cs.CV as the focus is on analyzing video data. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is relevant as the paper deals with analyzing video interviews, but it is less likely than cs.CV as the focus is on analyzing non-verbal behavior rather than multimedia content in general.
